    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.8.0-1210-gd367ed9b2\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nI don't use vim.\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nPop!_OS 22.04 LTS\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ngnome terminal 3.44.0 for gnome 42\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnvim.appimage\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvm install node\r\ncorepack enable\r\ncorepack prepare yarn@v3.2.4 --activate\r\nnpm install -g neovim\r\n\r\nnvim\r\n:checkhealth\r\n```\r\n\r\noutput:\r\n```\r\n## Node.js provider (optional)\r\n  - INFO: Node.js: v19.0.0\r\n  - INFO: Nvim node.js host: /home/user/.nvm/versions/node/v19.0.0/lib/node_modules/neovim/bin/cli.js\r\n  - ERROR: Command error (job=19, exit code 1): `yarn info neovim --json` (in '/home/user')\r\n    output: \u001b[31m\u001b[1mUsage Error\u001b[22m\u001b[39m: No project found in /home/user\u001b[1m$ \u001b[22myarn info [-A,--all] [-R,--recursive] [-X,--extra #0] [--cache] [--dependents] [--manifest] [--name-only] [--virtuals] [--json] ...\r\n  - ERROR: Failed to run: yarn info neovim --json\r\n    - ADVICE:\r\n      - Make sure you're connected to the internet.\r\n      - Are you behind a firewall or proxy?\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error generated:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"No project found\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNewer versions of yarn apparently do not have a concept of globally installing packages.  I am not sure what behavior would be best here.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nHonestly I am not sure to what degree this is actually a problem but not having the health check pass does bother me.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThat the health check pass using npm only perhaps?",
