            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "ah, `dlx` probably works like npm's `npx`. I suppose the Nvim nodejs provider could use `npx` or `dlx`.\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\n- remove yarn-related detection from the nodejs provider and :checkhealth\r\n- in :checkhealth, if yarn is detected on the system (and NOT npm), add an \"info\" message like \"dlx will be used to get the nodejs neovim package\"\r\n- in the nodejs provider,\r\n    - if npm is detected on the system but the neovim package is not found, use `npx` \r\n    - if yarn is detected on the system, `dlx`",
